parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
often without warning
and may restart after a few minutes. The vehicle may lose power
and the electrical system may continue to function. In some cases
the vehicle may experience a complete loss of power
including steering and brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, and loss of control.
symptoms: The engine overheats
and the temperature gauge moves into the red zone. The vehicle may experience a loss of power
and the engine may stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rod Bearing Failure and Engine Debris
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rod bearings can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The engine produces a knocking or ticking noise
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power. The engine may stall
and the check engine light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes loud clunking or grinding noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's lights
radio
or other accessories malfunction
the vehicle's battery drains quickly
the vehicle's engine stalls or dies
the vehicle's transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle's power steering and brakes malfunction
the vehicle's engine makes loud noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
